WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.210 --> 00:00:04.480
Tyrion Lannister is one of the most popular
characters in Game of Thrones, and for good

00:00:04.480 --> 00:00:09.670
reason. Tyrion is funny and clever, but also
flawed, and pained. He shows kindness to the

00:00:09.670 --> 00:00:13.280
vulnerable, and the back of his hand to dickheads
like Joffrey. He’s had a pretty rough time

00:00:13.280 --> 00:00:17.140
of it - he's been falsely accused of murder,
imprisoned, caught up in a war, then politics,

00:00:17.140 --> 00:00:20.749
ended up in another battle, had his face cut
up, was forced into a deeply uncomfortable

00:00:20.749 --> 00:00:24.359
marriage, was falsely accused of murder again,
betrayed by his lover, sentenced to death,

00:00:24.359 --> 00:00:28.309
and ended up killing his dad - or was it his
dad?

00:00:28.309 --> 00:00:33.760
Officially, Tyrion is the son of Tywin Lannister
and Tywin's cousin Joanna. But a controversial

00:00:33.760 --> 00:00:39.190
fan theory claims that Tyrion's real father
is the Mad King, Aerys Targeryen.

00:00:39.190 --> 00:00:43.100
So - back in the bad old days of the Mad King's
reign, the Targaryens were in charge, and

00:00:43.100 --> 00:00:48.280
young Joanna a companion of Rhaella, Aerys’
sister and eventual queen. Meanwhile, Tywin

00:00:48.280 --> 00:00:52.760
grew up frustrated with his father Lord Tytos,
who had a reputation for weakness, and was

00:00:52.760 --> 00:00:58.019
openly mocked to the point that Tywin began
to mistrust laughter itself. Tywin became

00:00:58.019 --> 00:01:03.069
determined to be the powerful, respected,
even feared man that his father was not. So

00:01:03.069 --> 00:01:06.840
he slaughtered the rebellious Tarbecks and
the Reynes of Castamere, began restoring the

00:01:06.840 --> 00:01:12.270
prestige and power of House Lannister, and
was made Hand of the King. Not long after,

00:01:12.270 --> 00:01:17.180
Tywin and Joanna were married. Tywin loved
Joanna. Apparently he smiled at their wedding,

00:01:17.180 --> 00:01:21.570
and Tywin doesn’t smile much. But something
else happened that night.

00:01:21.570 --> 00:01:25.540
According to Ser Barristan, who was Kingsguard
at the time, King Aerys “wanted” Joanna

00:01:25.540 --> 00:01:30.189
for years. At her wedding to Tywin, Aerys
made a drunken joke that implied he wanted

00:01:30.189 --> 00:01:35.110
to sleep with her, and later he took “liberties”.
We don’t know exactly what those “liberties”

00:01:35.110 --> 00:01:39.549
were. It probably wasn't sex, and it was too
early to have been Tyrion’s conception anyway.

00:01:39.549 --> 00:01:43.859
But what this shows is that King Aerys lusted
for Tyrion’s mother, and did something to

00:01:43.859 --> 00:01:48.590
her on her wedding night.
In A Storm of Swords, Joffrey tells Sansa that kings often

00:01:48.590 --> 00:01:53.969
sleep with whoever they want, including married
women. So King Aerys not only wanted Joanna,

00:01:53.969 --> 00:02:00.520
he probably could have had her. Aerys Targaryen
might have fathered Tyrion.

00:02:00.520 --> 00:02:03.609
But just quickly - it has been questioned
whether Joanna was even at King's Landing

00:02:03.609 --> 00:02:07.869
with Aerys at the time of Tyrion's conception.
It seems likely that she was, because Tywin

00:02:07.869 --> 00:02:11.140
presumably would’ve been there, as Hand
of the King, and Joanna must have been with

00:02:11.140 --> 00:02:15.530
Tywin if not Aerys for Tyrion's conception.
That said, Joanna was apparently at Casterly

00:02:15.530 --> 00:02:19.690
Rock “shortly” before giving birth to
Tyrion - she died giving birth to Tyrion,

00:02:19.690 --> 00:02:23.480
by the way. So it’s unclear. Maybe Joanna
was at King's Landing with Aerys and that's

00:02:23.480 --> 00:02:27.580
when Tyrion was conceived, or maybe Joanna
was at Casterly Rock the whole time, and it

00:02:27.580 --> 00:02:30.910
couldn’t have been Aerys. Or, for all we
know, Aerys could’ve fathered Tyrion at

00:02:30.910 --> 00:02:35.210
Casterly Rock, basically it’s inconclusive,
and it may have been Aerys.

00:02:35.210 --> 00:02:40.030
So if it was Aerys who fathered Tyrion, does
Tywin know? It's conceivable that he never

00:02:40.030 --> 00:02:45.160
knew - maybe Joanna was threatened into keeping
it secret - and Tywin's ignorance of Jamie

00:02:45.160 --> 00:02:49.010
and Cersei's relationship shows that he's
impressively good at being ignorant of the

00:02:49.010 --> 00:02:53.520
sexual proclivities of his loved ones - but
it makes a lot of sense if Tywin did know,

00:02:53.520 --> 00:02:57.360
firstly because he outright says it a couple
of times, and also because it explains Tywin's

00:02:57.360 --> 00:03:02.020
hatred for Tyrion. This hatred is usually
said to be because Tyrion killed Joanna in

00:03:02.020 --> 00:03:06.050
childbirth, which is kind of a ridiculous
reason to hate the kid, or he hates Tyrion

00:03:06.050 --> 00:03:10.460
for making a mockery of House Lannister by
publicly drinking and whoring. Even that is

00:03:10.460 --> 00:03:14.540
kinda hard to believe - Tywin has been an
absolute "cunt" to Tyrion well before Tyrion

00:03:14.540 --> 00:03:18.670
was drinking and whoring - Tyrion was just
sixteen when Tywin refused to let him travel

00:03:18.670 --> 00:03:22.460
and instead put him in charge of "all the
drains and cisterns within Casterly Rock",

00:03:22.460 --> 00:03:27.150
and just thirteen when he had Tyrion's love
Tysha raped by his guards. Like – fuck,

00:03:27.150 --> 00:03:30.850
who could do that to their own son? Jamie
and Cersei have their personality defects

00:03:30.850 --> 00:03:35.640
but Tywin doesn't do shit to them – not
without good reason, anyway. Further, Tywin

00:03:35.640 --> 00:03:40.150
disowns Tyrion, when Tywin is obsessed with
his legacy. Is it really worse for him to

00:03:40.150 --> 00:03:45.620
have Tyrion as an heir than no heir at all?
Tywin knowing - or suspecting - Tyrion to

00:03:45.620 --> 00:03:49.750
be Aerys' son makes all of this make sense
- when Aerys made Jamie Kingsguard, and therefore

00:03:49.750 --> 00:03:55.050
ineligible to inherit Casterly Rock, Aerys
made his bastard, Tyrion, the heir to Tywin's

00:03:55.050 --> 00:03:59.300
legacy. That spits in the face of everything
Tywin works for, so of course Tywin disowns

00:03:59.300 --> 00:04:02.900
Tyrion, of course he treats the Mad King's
son like shit, and of course he sacks Aerys'

00:04:02.900 --> 00:04:06.710
city shortly after the thing with Jamie. The
real question is why Tywin would allow Tyrion

00:04:06.710 --> 00:04:11.150
to live as a Lannister at all. Maybe because
despite being the Mad King's bastard, despite

00:04:11.150 --> 00:04:16.180
being a dwarf, Tyrion is Joanna's son, a Lannister,
and the son of the woman Tywin loved more

00:04:16.180 --> 00:04:20.889
than anything – it might even be a 'promise
me, Tywin' sort of a situation - so Tywin

00:04:20.889 --> 00:04:24.669
treats Tyrion pretty abhorrently, but still
ensures he lives a very comfortable life as

00:04:24.669 --> 00:04:28.539
a member of one of the great houses, funds
him with plenty of gold, and only tries to

00:04:28.539 --> 00:04:32.509
have him killed occasionally. Y’know, by
putting him on the front lines of this battle

00:04:32.509 --> 00:04:37.080
for no clear reason? Maybe Tywin figured that
way he could get rid of Tyrion without directly

00:04:37.080 --> 00:04:41.099
kinslaying. Anyway.
So here's the next piece of evidence - it's

00:04:41.099 --> 00:04:45.860
a common Targaryen trait to have dreams of
dragons, often prophetic dreams. Daenerys,

00:04:45.860 --> 00:04:50.830
Aemon, Daeron and Daemon Targaryen are all
known to have dragon dreams. The other character

00:04:50.830 --> 00:04:55.400
who dreams of dragons is Tyrion.
Tyrion's interest in dragons, though, is clearly

00:04:55.400 --> 00:04:59.409
a different thing to the dreams had by Dany
and others. There's no evidence of Tyrion

00:04:59.409 --> 00:05:03.919
having literal dreams about dragons at all,
certainly nothing like this stuff. The likely

00:05:03.919 --> 00:05:09.300
explanation is that Tyrion just liked dragons,
because - dragons are cool? The reference

00:05:09.300 --> 00:05:13.159
to Tyrion's dragon dreams is maybe a hint,
but it's not a strong one.

00:05:13.159 --> 00:05:17.639
So now Tyrion's appearance. Tyrion has “one
green eye and one black one” and hair that

00:05:17.639 --> 00:05:22.719
is both pale blond and black. Lannisters are
endlessly described as having golden-blond

00:05:22.719 --> 00:05:27.039
hair. But the pale-blond of Tyrion’s hair
seems more similar to Targaryen hair, which

00:05:27.039 --> 00:05:31.259
is generally described as silver-blond. It
might be silly to pay this much attention

00:05:31.259 --> 00:05:35.289
to hair colour, but as we were taught in the
first book, "seed is strong", and hair colour

00:05:35.289 --> 00:05:40.080
can tell a lot about someone's parentage.
Tyrion's pale-blond hair is more similar to

00:05:40.080 --> 00:05:44.080
Targaryen silver than Lannister gold, so that
could be a hint to his parentage.

00:05:44.080 --> 00:05:47.659
So Tyrion also has mismatched eyes. There's
another character with mismatched eyes in

00:05:47.659 --> 00:05:53.629
the Song - Shiera Seastar, a bastard of Aegon
IV Targaryen. And like the two-coloured hair,

00:05:53.629 --> 00:05:58.520
the two-coloured eyes could symbolically indicate
Tyrion's mixed blood. Maybe.

00:05:58.520 --> 00:06:02.430
A final note on his appearance - it's been
suggested that Tyrion's dwarfism might be

00:06:02.430 --> 00:06:07.310
the result of Targaryen genetic weirdness,
or possibly the result of attempted abortion.

00:06:07.310 --> 00:06:10.610
Dunno how biology works in the world of ice
and fire, but we have no precedent for either

00:06:10.610 --> 00:06:14.409
of those things occurring so they don't seem
strong pieces of evidence.

00:06:14.409 --> 00:06:19.779
A final hint, and possibly a big one - if
Tyrion is a Targaryen, he could fit very nicely

00:06:19.779 --> 00:06:24.449
into the prophecy of the three heads of the
dragon. Tyrion, Dany and Jon are the three

00:06:24.449 --> 00:06:29.300
main characters. They all have Targaryen blood.
Each of their mothers died in childbirth,

00:06:29.300 --> 00:06:33.289
each of them have had to kill someone they
love, each could correspond to one of the

00:06:33.289 --> 00:06:37.009
three living dragons, with which they could
fulfil the prophecy, unite the Seven Kingdoms

00:06:37.009 --> 00:06:41.960
and defeat the evil Others and ride off for
a party on the Summer Isles. Or something.

00:06:41.960 --> 00:06:46.330
It seems to work, but does it suit the cynical
world George R. R. Martin has created? Does

00:06:46.330 --> 00:06:49.639
the ridiculed, disempowered dwarf have to
turn out to be a magical dragon prince who

00:06:49.639 --> 00:06:53.740
saves the day, or can he have value just as
a man?

00:06:53.740 --> 00:06:57.389
Are prophecies really even a thing anyway?
Do they magically influence peoples' destinies

00:06:57.389 --> 00:07:01.300
in the Song of Ice and Fire, or do people
fulfil them through their knowledge of them?

00:07:01.300 --> 00:07:05.120
We're several thousand pages in and we've
still never really clearly seen prophecy at

00:07:05.120 --> 00:07:10.620
work, so the 'three heads of the dragon' seem
a shaky reason to believe Tyrion to be a Targaryen.

00:07:10.620 --> 00:07:15.189
One of the main reasons why the theory ultimately
is doubtful is that while Tyrion being a Targaryen

00:07:15.189 --> 00:07:20.050
bastard does make his awful relationship with
Tywin easier to understand, it makes it something

00:07:20.050 --> 00:07:26.080
less. Genna Lannister says that, more than
Jamie, Tyrion is Tywin's true son. Tyrion

00:07:26.080 --> 00:07:31.289
has all of Tywin's cunning, calculating nature,
and political skill, but in the form of a

00:07:31.289 --> 00:07:35.819
dwarf which Tywin – so sensitive to mockery
and the appearance of weakness – cannot

00:07:35.819 --> 00:07:40.490
bring himself to respect. There's so much
irony in that Tyrion's drinking and whoring

00:07:40.490 --> 00:07:45.300
is surely a consequence of his brutal mistreatment
by his father, making him feel worthless and

00:07:45.300 --> 00:07:50.499
unloved. But the vices that Tywin hates Tyrion
for are vices not only that he caused but

00:07:50.499 --> 00:07:55.599
that he shares. Remember – Tyrion found
Shae in Tywin’s bed before he killed her

00:07:55.599 --> 00:08:00.659
- which mirrors something Tywin hated his
father Tytos for. Late in life, Tytos took

00:08:00.659 --> 00:08:05.419
a common woman as a mistress, and let her
steal his dead wife’s jewellery. After Tytos’

00:08:05.419 --> 00:08:09.339
death, Tywin punished the woman cruelly, running
her naked through the streets of Lannisport

00:08:09.339 --> 00:08:13.629
and forcing her to publicly confess to being
“a thief and a harlot”. So then late in

00:08:13.629 --> 00:08:17.809
his own life after the death of his own wife
Tywin sleeps with a common woman, and lets

00:08:17.809 --> 00:08:22.050
her wear his jewellery, the Hand of the King
necklace. What Tywin hates in Tyrion is what

00:08:22.050 --> 00:08:28.370
he recognises in himself. When Tywin sits
there, bleeding out, resolutely not shitting

00:08:28.370 --> 00:08:32.870
gold, and tells Tyrion "you are ... no son
of mine", it doesn't mean Tyrion is a secret

00:08:32.870 --> 00:08:38.270
Targaryen bastard - it means something much
more. It means Tywin has rejected his trueborn

00:08:38.270 --> 00:08:43.580
son, refused him and tormented him because
he could not bear to look upon a twisted version

00:08:43.580 --> 00:08:48.100
of himself.
And then Tyrion murders Tywin with all the

00:08:48.100 --> 00:08:54.570
cold brutality of his father.
It's tragic, it's complex, it's "the human

00:08:54.570 --> 00:08:58.640
heart in conflict with itself", it's what
George R. R. Martin's writing is really all

00:08:58.640 --> 00:09:04.890
about, not dragon riding and happy endings.
So yes, Tyrion has some kind-of-Targaryen-ish

00:09:04.890 --> 00:09:08.840
characteristics, and yes it's conceivable
that King Aerys, old dirty bastard that he

00:09:08.840 --> 00:09:13.130
is, forced himself on Joanna and fathered
Tyrion. But there's no really strong evidence,

00:09:13.130 --> 00:09:17.230
and it cheapens one of the most interesting
relationships in the series. So for these

00:09:17.230 --> 00:09:21.820
reasons, it seems possible but quite unlikely
that Tyrion is a Targaryen.

00:09:21.820 --> 00:09:28.000
Thanks for watching this video. If you'd like
to see more, subscribe, or share and follow

00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:30.220
on Facebook and Twitter. Thanks.

